{"sequence":51,"timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:22:19.889457399Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-8798c01f","body":"finding_summary: Paths returned by `git ls-files -z ...` are byte strings, but the new ignored-path filtering lossy-decodes them to `String` before feeding them back to `git update-index --force-remove`. That breaks tracked gitignored and assume-unchanged files whose names are not valid UTF-8: the temporary checkpoint index keeps the original raw path, so the checkpoint still leaks that file. I reproduced this with a temp repo containing `bad\\xff.txt`, where removing the lossy-decoded name exits 0 but the raw path remains in the index.\naffected_files: `src/adapters/worktree.rs:134-138`, `src/adapters/worktree.rs:148-157`, `src/adapters/worktree.rs:170-174`, `tests/unit/checkpoint_test.rs:289-358`\nremediation_hint: Preserve raw path bytes / `OsString` values through the round-trip and pass them back to Git without UTF-8 conversion, for example by building command args from `OsStrExt::from_bytes` or by using a NUL-delimited stdin path channel.","dedup_key":"60fff7c4242e547143e5045fac13ddccd841286cc5293b72d2368b3783888287","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260421224108","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
