{"sequence":105,"timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:40:24.625010086Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-4-f5a0ed29","body":"`src/adapters/worktree.rs:142-152` narrows tracked ignored-path detection to `git ls-files -i -c --exclude-per-directory=.gitignore`, and `build_checkpoint_tree` only removes the paths returned by that scan (`src/adapters/worktree.rs:269-274`). That means tracked files ignored via other standard Git ignore sources, notably `.git/info/exclude` and `core.excludesFile`, still survive into checkpoint commits. The new tests at `tests/unit/checkpoint_test.rs:437-533` explicitly lock in that narrower behavior. The bead requires the standard-ignore behavior (`--exclude-standard` or equivalent), so this leaves `rb: checkpoint` incomplete and still able to leak unrelated locally ignored tracked files into diffs.","dedup_key":"1c3d65c9867a0ae0b75aad3f32d8e2edafd65be4c4a11207664b0302d460d6a5","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260421224108","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
