{"sequence":131,"timestamp":"2026-04-22T02:17:01.005221343Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-5-ed34cdf0","body":"finding_summary: `build_checkpoint_tree` deletes tracked-but-gitignored files from checkpoint commits instead of preserving their parent blob. `src/adapters/worktree.rs:263-268` unconditionally `update-index --force-remove`s every tracked ignored path after `read-tree` loaded the parent tree, so a checkpoint/reset turns any still-tracked ignored file into a real deletion. The new assertions in `tests/unit/checkpoint_test.rs:352-385` and `tests/unit/checkpoint_test.rs:437-525` lock in that destructive behavior.\naffected_files:\n- src/adapters/worktree.rs:263-268\n- tests/unit/checkpoint_test.rs:352-385\n- tests/unit/checkpoint_test.rs:437-525\nremediation_hint: Keep tracked gitignored paths at their parent/index entry in the temporary index, the same way assume-unchanged paths are restored, and compute the ignored set from the pre-staging tracked state so ignored edits/deletions do not leak without deleting the tracked file from the checkpoint tree.","dedup_key":"2f64f272b70b129a763713c2f746a6285e8c0e441a410c6584aba333632b14f5","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260421224108","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
